cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of private classification, which is a subfield of machine learning and privacy. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are all likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new notion of algorithmic stability, which may be of independent interest, suggesting that cs.IT (Information Theory) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses an application of their results to boosting the privacy and accuracy parameters of differentially-private learners, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
